# ============================================================================
# Usage Instructions
# ============================================================================

# 1. BACKUP your current pyproject.toml:
#    cp pyproject.toml pyproject.toml.backup
#
# 2. MERGE the sections above into your pyproject.toml
#
# 3. INSTALL updated dependencies:
#    poetry add --group dev mypy types-PyYAML coverage pytest-cov pre-commit
#
# 4. RUN initial check (will show many errors):
#    poetry run ruff check michelangelo/ --select ALL
#
# 5. FIX auto-fixable issues:
#    poetry run ruff check michelangelo/ --fix --select I,UP,W,F
#
# 6. GRADUALLY enable stricter rules:
#    - Start with I (import sorting)
#    - Then UP (pyupgrade)
#    - Then B (bugbear)
#    - Finally D (docstrings) and ANN (annotations)
#
# 7. SETUP pre-commit:
#    poetry run pre-commit install
#
# 8. RUN on all files:
#    poetry run pre-commit run --all-files
#
# 9. ENABLE mypy:
#    poetry run mypy michelangelo/ --show-error-codes
#
# 10. TRACK progress:
#     - Create GitHub issues for each module to update
#     - Track type coverage with mypy reports
#     - Monitor ruff violation counts over time
